reviews.text: Nice place overall, with good dinners. Also - the balcony is great and allows for enjoying the weather during the day. Cheap lunches, of standard Japanese style, and decent Japan-influenced drinks options too. The broader cocktail menu is also highly recommended to try out as you should find something of high quality there to your tastes.
Very low quality Hong Kong style Japanese restaurant. Both service was and food quality were below average. Don't think I will ever come back again.
Friendly staff, nice atmosphere, the food is fresh. Not bad.

This is my fifth time to choose Tenkei as our dining restaurant. We had unforgettable experience in the previous visits due to the excellent service and food quality. I kept recommending Tenkei to my friends, colleagues and family.
 
 Unfortunately, we are totally disappointed this time. At March 26 2019 7pm, we booked our seats for five people with 50% discount. We suddenly had one more friend to join us, so we asked the reception staff to help us to arrange for that.
 
 However, the attitude of the reception staff, female in brown hair with chubby face, was extremely bad. We expected the staff would help us to arrange and provide the best arrangement for us. But the sentences we got from the staff, were “no” and “can’t”. Worse still, she asked us to sit separately but there are lots of unoccupied seats and tables. Last time we could combine two different booking into one table (15 people in total).
 
 Due to the poor experience this time, I would not recommend Tenkei to others anymore, as long as there is no acceptable reply from Tenkei.

I came here with a group of six people for drinks and shisha and I'd give this place 0 stars if I could. The service was terrible even though the place was almost empty, the waiters seemed like they'd just been hired the day before and had no idea what was going on, the drinks were inconsistent, the bar snacks were bland, and even though we paid for one of the more expensive shisha flavors with a champagne base it tasted like a cheap mint shisha. They also have a 300hkd minimum charge per person which is not difficult to reach given their prices. I'd honestly rather drink a beer next to a 7/11 than go here.

reviews.text: Okay club although they pulled one of those famous scams where they "create" an event and start charging cover for it even though it should be free entry according to some local students I've met. I've been in a lot of clubs around Europe and the States and this one seems less professional in terms of just trying to have fun. The entry staff treats you like a little kid although I don't know if that is just an Asian culture thing or not but as a grown man, I don't need to be told what to do (at least in Europe and the States the staff assumes I am half competent). This club is linked to Play I believe. Clean bathrooms at least.
I got here after a relaxing massage, I have lost of the relax benefit. It is a Club ok, but I didn't have a good feeling. Maybe it was just yesterday night. You can try.....

Absolutely terrible experience tonight with the bouncer. We had bought tickets before for a student party. There was no information that passports were the only accepted ids for foreigners. As exchange students we do not have HK IDs. We were not provided a refund. I was nearly attacked by the bouncer for suggesting that his ID would be accepted in Ireland, my country. 0/10. Do not recommend to anyone seeking to protect their money, their own safety, and fun.
The club was full and there were no space for breathing.

I visted there on Thursday, I looked for no one after I had washed my eyes. 
I think that was like the last sip of the beer.

reviews.text:
係openrice 見到最大路嘅刺身魚鮫冷盤等等全部都無。勉強揀左幾樣串燒都唔係樣樣有。野飲：啤酒- 無，菠蘿汁- 都要另開問一問先知有定無，跟menu 叫架啦已經！
串燒煮物只係室溫，唔熱嘅。溏心蛋：好鹹，7仔買到嘅都比佢好食。eatigo 半價左都$350，似乎等結業，求求其其賣埋啲貨尾算數。

Nice place overall, with good dinners. Also - the balcony is great and allows for enjoying the weather during the day. Cheap lunches, of standard Japanese style, and decent Japan-influenced drinks options too. The broader cocktail menu is also highly recommended to try out as you should find something of high quality there to your tastes.
有50%折扣嘅話就ok，野食夠熱，中間細枱較迫，員工有禮貌

午飯時間和同事來到了天慶，一家新開的酒吧。因為時候尚早，所以人不多。

餐廳很大，螢幕播着櫻花落下的動態，陽台外面放置了櫻花樹，頗有日式風情。

我們點了一個吞拿魚丼，一個炸雞蛋飯。上菜時間不算耐，賣相也頗精緻。先來的是沙律，主菜配上了麵豉湯和南瓜天婦羅。

吞拿魚當有八大塊吞拿魚，配上三文魚子，簡單而不失美味。

炸雞便當好豐富，包括一個蛋包飯，炸雞件和炸南瓜餅，還有麵豉湯和炸南瓜。炸雞外脆內多汁，做得不錯！南瓜餅也香脆！

想不到酒吧的午餐可以做得這麼日式。跟餐還附有甜品蜜桃雪葩，清新又清甜，食完炸嘢來一口清涼的雪葩，消暑由解膩。

這裏環境不錯，而且酒品選擇豐富，有不同的啤酒及COCKTAIL提供，下次放工可以和同事再來碰個杯底！
Very low quality Hong Kong style Japanese restaurant. Both service was and food quality were below average. Don't think I will ever come back again.
